excerpt: This ancient sandstone fort on a plateau features towers & a Hindu temple dedicated to Kali.
detail_description: Bahu Fort, an ancient sandstone fort located on a plateau in Jammu, is home to a Hindu temple dedicated to Goddess Kali. The fort overlooks the old city of Jammu and houses the small and compact white-marble temple believed to have been built in the 8th or 9th century. Although not open to the public due to security reasons, visitors can still view this historic temple.
name: Bahu Fort
address: Gorkha Nagar, Jammu, 180006

excerpt: Sprawling palace complex, parts of which date to 1824, that mixes Rajasthani & European styles.
detail_description: Govind Sharma is a sprawling palace complex that beautifully blends Rajasthani and European architectural styles, with parts dating back to 1824. It is a wonderful historic site in Jammu, featuring the old Bahu Fort, the golden-covered Hindu Raghunath Temple, sacred Peer Baba, Sri Amarnath Ji holy cave, and ornate Mubarak Mandi Palace.
name: Mubarak Mandi Palace
address: Mubarak mandi, Panjtirthi, Jammu, Jammu and Kashmir 180001

excerpt: Stately museum & former royal palace with fine art, antique books & a gold throne.
detail_description: Nestled on a hillside overlooking the Tawi River, the Amar Mahal Museum and Library is a stunning architectural gem that once served as the royal residence of the Dogra dynasty. Built in the 1800s by Raja Amar Singh, this magnificent palace showcases an impressive blend of European-style architecture and striking red sandstone. Today, it stands as a museum filled with exquisite art pieces, antique books, and even a gold throne that reflects its regal past.
name: Amar Mahal Museum and Library
address: PVXC+3WM, Palace Rd, Karan Nagar, Jammu, Jammu and Kashmir 180001

detail_description: Raghunath Temple, located in Raghunath market, is a significant religious site dedicated to Lord Rama. Built by the J&K Hindu king in the 18th century, this historic temple complex houses seven smaller temples within its premises. Managed by the Dharmarth Trust, it boasts impressive architecture with pointed roof structures and intricate carvings that draw numerous visitors seeking blessings from Lord Sri Ram and other deities enshrined within.
name: RAGHUNATH TEMPLE
address: JWV6+GF3, Bari Brahmana, Jammu, Jammu and Kashmir 181133

excerpt: Jammu is a city in Indian-administered Jammu and Kashmir in the disputed Kashmir region. It is the winter capital of Jammu and Kashmir, which is an Indian-administered union territory. It is the headquarters and the largest city in Jammu district. Wikipedia.
detail_description: Jammu, located in the disputed Kashmir region, serves as the winter capital of Jammu and Kashmir, an Indian-administered union territory. As the largest city in Jammu district, it is a significant hub with cultural and administrative importance. This city offers a blend of historical significance and modern developments, making it an intriguing destination to explore.
name: Jammu

detail_description: Bagh-E-Bahu is a stunning garden located near the iconic Bahu Fort in Jammu. It offers a serene and romantic atmosphere with its sprawling lawns, grand fountains, charming stone sculptures, beautiful lake, and large aquarium. The garden was originally laid out in the 19th century and is known for its scenic beauty and historical significance. Visitors can enjoy the peaceful surroundings while taking in views of Bahu Fort and the Tawi River.
name: Bagh-E-Bahu
address: Bahu Fort, Bagh-e-bahu, near hanuman mandir, Jammu, Jammu and Kashmir 180006

detail_description: Nestled in the picturesque hills of Jammu and Kashmir, Vaishnodevi Temple, also known as Shri Mata Vaishno Devi Temple, is a Hindu pilgrimage site dedicated to Vaishno Devi, a manifestation of Durga. Situated at an altitude of 5200 feet on Trikuta hill, this sacred haven attracts millions of devotees annually.
name: Vaishnodevi Temple
address: PVMC+3PQ, Pir Mitha Mastgarh, Pakki Dhaki, Old Heritage City, Jammu, 180001

excerpt: Heritage museum in Mubarak Mandi Palace showcasing Dogra cultural artifacts & miniature paintings.
detail_description: Nestled within the historic Mubarak Mandi Palace complex in Jammu, the Dogra Art Museum is a treasure trove of cultural artifacts and miniature paintings that offer a glimpse into the rich heritage of the Dogra dynasty. With an extensive collection of art, historical memorabilia, and artifacts from the region, this museum serves as a vital repository for preserving and promoting the artistic legacy of the area.
name: Dogra Art Museum
address: Panjtirthi, Jammu, Jammu and Kashmir 180001

excerpt: Large, historic Hindu temple built in 1883 with an 8-ft. stone lingam representing Shiva.
detail_description: Nestled in the vibrant heart of Jammu city, the Shree Ranbireshwar Temple stands as a magnificent testament to Hindu architecture and devotion. Constructed in 1883 by Maharaja Ranbir Singh, this historic shrine is dedicated to Lord Shiva and features an impressive 8-foot tall Shivling crafted from black marble. As one of the oldest temples in the region, it draws countless devotees who come to experience its serene beauty and spiritual ambiance.
name: Shree Ranbireshwar Temple Shri Ranbireshwar Temple, Niranjani Akhara.
address: PVM7+WPM, shalamar Road near ciivil secretariat, Jammu

excerpt: Tiny zoo with species such as crocodiles, cobras, deer & tigers in old-school enclosures.
detail_description: Manda Zoo Park, located near the Hari Niwas Palace, offers a unique opportunity to connect with nature. The zoo features various wildlife species in natural-like enclosures, allowing animals to feel safe and comfortable. Visitors can enjoy watching wild animals roaming freely and vibrant birds creating a cacophony of sounds. The zoo is popular among families and animal lovers for its diverse range of mammals and birds.
name: Manda Zoo Park
address: near Harinivas, Palace Rd, Janipur, Jammu, Jammu and Kashmir 180007

detail_description: Ramnagar Wildlife Sanctuary, located in the Jammu region, is a stunning haven for bird enthusiasts and nature lovers. The sanctuary boasts a diverse range of bird species such as Indian Peafowl, Pheasants, Indian Mynah, Red Junglefowl and Chakor. Spanning 31.50 square kilometers, it is home to various mammals including Nilgai, Barking Deer, Wild Boar and Rhesus Monkey.
name: Ramnagar Wildlife Sanctuary
address: Jammu, near Hotel Jammu Ashok

detail_description: Nathatop is a picturesque hill station that transforms into a winter wonderland, perfect for skiing and paragliding. Shiva Cafe, nestled in the mountains, offers breathtaking views and an enchanting atmosphere for a memorable experience. It stands out for its exceptional hospitality and provides everything from food to camping facilities. Visitors praise it as a place of unparalleled peace and tranquility.
name: Shiva cafe Nathatop
address: Hno. 219 chowk chabutra, Jammu, Jammu and Kashmir 180001

detail_description: Maha Maya Temple in Jammu stands out from traditional Hindu temples as it is a tribute to a local heroine who bravely fought against foreign invaders centuries ago. Situated by the Tawi river and nestled behind Bahu Fort, this unique temple offers a serene and holy atmosphere with stunning views of the surrounding mountains and the river. Visitors can also enjoy an exhilarating ropeway ride from Bahu Fort to reach the temple.
name: Maha Maya Temple
address: PVJR+66H, Maha Maya Path, Jammu, Jammu and Kashmir 180017

detail_description: Nestled along the banks of the Tawi River in Jammu, Peer Kho Cave Temple is a captivating destination that beckons both devotees and history enthusiasts alike. This ancient temple, believed to date back over 5,000 years and possibly linked to the Mahabharata era, is carved into a natural cave adorned with striking rock formations that create an enchanting atmosphere.
name: Peer Kho
address: Jammu 180001

detail_description: Raghunath Temple, located in Jammu, is a significant symbol of devotion dedicated to Lord Rama. It is one of the largest temple complexes in North India and houses Lord Raghunath along with 33 koti gods and their families. The temple complex also includes separate shrines for Lord Shiva and Mata Baglamuki. Maintained neatly, the white-painted temple follows Vedic architectural styles prevalent in North India.
name: Shri Raghunath Temple, Jammu
address: PVJ6+6Q5, Raghunath mandir chowk Jammu city, Jammu and Kashmir 180001

detail_description: Peer Baba Dargah, also known as the durgah of Peer Budhan Ali Shah, is a sacred site dedicated to the Islamic saint who reportedly lived for 500 years surviving solely on milk. This revered place attracts followers from various faiths, including Hindus and Sikhs who seek blessings from Peer Baba. It is believed that the saint had connections with Guru Gobind Singh, further adding to its significance for devotees.
name: Peer Baba Dargah
address: PQMC+XR9, Sarora, 181206

detail_description: Dudhadhari Mandir, located on a hilltop in Jammu, is a beautiful temple built in memory of Dudhadhari Baba, a local saint who sustained himself solely on milk. The temple offers stunning views of the surrounding areas and is made of white marble. It's known for its serene atmosphere and fresh breeze from the northern region. Visitors can also visit an ashram associated with the temple in Haridwar, which houses many cows.
name: Dudhadhari Mandir
address: MVV6+R4R, Shastri Nagar, Jammu, Jammu and Kashmir 180004

detail_description: Dargah Garib Shah, located in the heart of Jammu city, is a significant religious site honoring the Sufi saint Baba Garib Shah. This Muslim shrine houses his Samadhi and is revered by both Muslims and Hindus, with the latter community taking care of its maintenance. It stands as a testament to the spiritual harmony and reverence for Sufi traditions in the region.
name: Dargah
address: PVH7+XC7, Residency Rd, Shalamar, Prem Nagar, Old Heritage City, Jammu, Jammu and Kashmir 180001

detail_description: Sidhra Golf Course in Jammu is a picturesque and tranquil spot, boasting lush greenery and beautifully manicured golfing areas. The 18-hole course spans about 6700 yards with well-laid out roughs and strategically placed sand traps. Visitors can enjoy the scenic beauty while dining with family and friends, making it a unique experience. The facility also offers amenities such as a coffee place, good toilets, adequate parking, and the option to prebook tee times and caddies.
name: Sidhra Golf Course
address: Jammu-Kunjwani Bypass Rd, Jammu and Kashmir 180019

detail_description: Jammu Haat is a vibrant cultural center in the heart of the city, offering a diverse array of handicrafts, handlooms, and delectable local cuisines. Modeled after traditional Indian marketplaces, it serves as a platform for artisans to showcase their exquisite craftsmanship and promote indigenous arts and crafts. Visitors can marvel at the wide range of handcrafted products unique to the region, including intricately designed textiles, wood carvings, colorful paintings, and delicate jewelry.
name: Jammu Haat
address: Gulab Singh Marg, near DOGRA CHOWK, Prem Nagar, Old Heritage City, Jammu, Jammu and Kashmir 180001

detail_description: Ganesh ki hawali Dessa Doda is a comprehensive travel guide that covers various cities and their attractions in the Jammu and Kashmir region. From the popular destinations of Srinagar, Gulmarg, and Pahalgam to lesser-known gems like Anantnag, Bandipora, and Doda, this guide provides detailed information about each place.
name: Ganesh ki hawali Dessa Doda
address: PVG4+JRR, Kolohand, Jammu, 180016

detail_description: Carlcare_TECNO, Infinix, itel Phone Repair in Baramulla, Jammu & Kashmir is a service center that caters to various cities including Srinagar, Gulmarg, Sonmarg, Pahalgam, Anantnag and more. The center offers repair services for TECNO, Infinix and itel phones in the region.
name: Carlcare_TECNO, Infinix, itel Phone Repair (Baramulla, Jammu & Kashmir)
